# Line endings are pinned to LF in the repository so that the tree is identical
# on every platform. Chromium development requires core.autocrlf=false, which
# means git stops normalising on checkout — without this file, a CRLF working
# copy silently shows every line of a file as modified.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Patches are applied by `git apply`, which requires byte-exact context. Any
# line-ending conversion corrupts them, so they are never transformed.
*.patch -text

# Binary assets.
*.png binary
*.ico binary
*.icns binary
